added.title: Pool's Out for Summer
added.description: The boys go to the Aberdale Community Pool for a day of wet fun! While Jeff slowly wades in the shallow end, getting used to the water, Sumo tries to conquer the diving board, redeeming himself from last summer's bellyflop, and Clarence sneaks past the lifeguards into the hot tub for a boiling surprise…

added.title: Attack the Block Party
added.description: Clarence, Jeff and Sumo investigate a high school party down the street, which they mistake for an alien invasion.

added.title: The Tails of Mardrynia
added.description: After reading a book about a mystical animal society in class, Clarence is inspired to round up local animals and recreate an animal world of his own to cheer up his friend Percy. But will Percy take the game too far?

added.title: Too Gross for Comfort
added.description: Clarence's innocent attempt to ingratiate Chelsea, a girl, into a boys only tree fort puts Sumo in charge of an effort to gross Chelsea out and preserve the status quo.

added.title: Rough Riders Elementary
added.description: When a corporate sponsorship of Clarence's school turns into an ominous corporate takeover, Clarence must stand up to the the man, no matter how tasty the chicken may be.

added.title: Bedside Manners
added.description: After a nasty spill lands Belson in a full body cast, Clarence pays his bedridden friend a visit at the hospital, but what Clarence thinks will cheer him up might actually drive Belson totally crazy!

added.title: Suspended
added.description: Clarence and Sumo hit the jackpot when they get suspended for a week, learning all sorts of different facts they'd never learn in class, but after a few days the suspension takes its toll, boredom sets in and the boys want to go back.

added.title: Goldfish Follies
added.description: Clarence buys a goldfish, but when the goldfish bag breaks before he can get home, Clarence must keep his new friend out of harms way and get him back into water before it's too late.

added.title: Hairence
added.description: It's time for Clarence's first summer job helping out his mom at Hip Clipz Salon School, but when a rude customer bosses around Mary and her staff, Clarence gives her a haircut she'll never forget.

added.title: Firework Run
added.description: Mordecai, Rigby and Muscle Man have to get fireworks for an event at the park because they used the ones Benson got.

added.title: In the House
added.description: Rigby eggs the wrong house and gets cursed by a wizard.

added.title: Weekend at Benson's
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby accidentally knock out Benson and try to cover it up.

added.title: Ello Gov'nor
added.description: After watching a scary movie about a British Taxi, the guys have to help Rigby overcome his fears.

added.title: Do Me a Solid
added.description: Mordecai owes Rigby big time when he agrees to go on a double date with him.

added.title: Really Real Wrestling
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to go see wrestling, but they have to take care of Pops.

added.title: The Night Owl
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby go to unbelievable lengths to beat Muscle Man and High Five Ghost in a radio contest to win a car.

added.title: First Day
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby play Rock, Paper, Scissors for a chair.

added.title: The Unicorns Have Got to Go
added.description: In order to impress Margret and ask her out, Mordecai hangs with a bunch of punk Unicorns who say they can help him get his lady.

removed.title: Game Show
removed.description: While shopping with his Mom, Clarence discovers Breehn hiding in a clothes rack. Under the guise of trying on new clothes for their moms, they sneak out to find a local gameshow being hosted inside the Aberdale Mall.

removed.title: Motel
removed.description: Following an insect mishap Clarence's house needs to be fumigated forcing Mary, Chad, and Clarence into a motel. In the meantime, Clarence and Chad learn a bit about responsibility while Mary contemplates a life of letting go.

removed.title: Man of the House
removed.description: Clarence's first night home alone spirals out of control, forcing Clarence and his pals to wage war against their own home security measures.

removed.title: Dream Boat
removed.description: Sumo devotes himself to the Sisyphean task of building a boat, defying the expectations of everyone in his life, including himself.

removed.title: Rock Show
removed.description: Chad's band Dogmon, plays a show for the first time in years, giving Clarence and Mary a chance to really rock out.

removed.title: The Boxcurse Children
removed.description: Clarence, Jeff, and Sumo stumble upon a mysterious box. After they open it, some strange things begin to happen. Convinced they've unlocked a curse, they become determined to reverse it!

removed.title: Sumo Goes West
removed.description: Clarence learns his best friend Sumo may transfer to another school! It's up to Clarence to protest, petition and rally to convince everyone to let Sumo stay - or face losing his closest school pal!

removed.title: Clarence for President
removed.description: It's school election time at Aberdale Elementary, and Jeff is once again determined to become Class President. However like previous years, he's unsuccessful in connecting with other kid. That is until he sees a shoe-in puppet President, the lovable Clarence!

removed.title: Stump Brothers
removed.description: After Clarence and Sumo cause a power outage in Sumo's family home, they're sent off in the hot desert with Sumo's older brother to retrieve a generator part. Will they survive the trek or will Sumo's sibling rivalry boil over?

removed.title: Cruisin
removed.description: Mordecai and Rigby make a bet with Margaret and Eileen that they can get a girl's phone number by cruising.

removed.title: Temp Check
removed.description: Rigby hires a temp to do his work but gets jealous when the temp becomes tight with Mordecai.

removed.title: Benson Be Gone
removed.description: Mordecai sees Pops naked and goes on a quest to unsee what he has seen.

removed.title: Slam Dunk
removed.description: Mordecai needs access to the computer so he and Rigby challenge Muscle Man and High Five Ghost to a basketball game for a week's worth of computer time.

removed.title: Rap It Up
removed.description: Mordecai and Rigby don't want Pops to be called a loser so they say that they'll join him in a rap battle.

removed.title: But I Have a Receipt
removed.description: When a bad game ruins game night, M & R attempt to return it to a not-so-pleasant store manager.

removed.title: Muscle Woman
removed.description: Mordecai & Rigby attempt to get Muscle Man and his girlfriend back together, until she begins to fall for Mordecai.

removed.title: High Score
removed.description: Mordecai and Rigby need to find a new TV in order to defeat the hardest video game ever.

removed.title: Do or Diaper
removed.description: Mordecai has to kiss Margaret by the end of the week or else wear a diaper.
